{{refimprove|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox book | name = Defenders of the Faith | image = Defenders of the Faith coverthumb.jpg | caption = Cover of ''Defenders of the Faith'' | author = Rich Redman, James Wyatt | genre = [[Role-playing game]] | publisher = Wizards of the Coast | release_date = May 2001 | media_type = Print ([[Trade paper edition|Trade Paperback]]) | pages = 96 | isbn = 0-7869-1840-3 }} {{italic title|noerror|all=yes}} <!-- template after the infobox to prevent the display of error message --> '''''Defenders of the Faith: A Guidebook to Clerics and Paladins''''' is an optional rulebook for the [[Editions of Dungeons & Dragons#Dungeons & Dragons 3rd edition|3rd edition]] of ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'', and notable for its [[paperback|trade paperback]] format.
==Contents== The guidebook provides supplemental information for characters belonging to the [[Cleric (Dungeons & Dragons)|Cleric]] and [[Paladin (Dungeons & Dragons)|Paladin]] base classes. This book introduced Divine Feats, which are still used in version 3.5. This book also contained tips for creating and playing characters of the aforementioned class, as well as several prestige classes.
==Publication history== The book was designed by [[Rich Redman]] and [[James Wyatt (game designer)|James Wyatt]], and was published in 2001 by [[Wizards of the Coast]]. Cover art was by [[Gerald Brom|Brom]], with interior art by [[Dennis Cramer]].
Although it was not updated to 3.5 Edition, most of the book's prestige classes were reintroduced in the 3.5 supplemental sourcebook ''[[Complete Divine]]''.
==Reception== The reviewer from ''[[Pyramid (magazine)|Pyramid]]'' found the advice on effectively playing clerics and paladins useful, even if it "rarely goes beyond the basics information", and found the section on special paladin mounts to be one of the most interesting areas.<ref>http://www.sjgames.com/pyramid/sample.html?id=2289</ref>
